record_data.record_plain_text: Antelope Expansion 2, LLC Electric MBR Agreements Effective Date: August 16, 2018 Service Agreement Option Code A Attachment 1: Antelope Expansion 2, LLC Service Agreement Execution Service Agreement (Antelope Expansion 2, LLC) This Service Agreement, dated as of August 1, 2018, is entered into, by and between Big Sky North, LLC (the “Interconnection Provider”), and Antelope Expansion 2, LLC (“User”). Reference is made to the Master Interconnection Services Agreement, dated as of August 1, 2018 (the “Master Interconnection Services Agreement”), by and among the Interconnection Provider and the other parties thereto. Capitalized terms used herein but not otherwise defined shall have the meanings assigned to such terms in the Master Interconnection Services Agreement. 1.0 Interconnection Provider shall provide 105 MW (“Reserved Capacity”) of firm transmission service to User for an initial term of 35 calendar years (the “Service Term”) following the Service Commencement Date, after the expiration of which such service shall be extended on a year-to-year basis until terminated by User upon sixty (60) days prior written notice or upon the mutual agreement of Interconnection Provider and User. 2.0 User is an Eligible Customer under the Master Interconnection Services Agreement. 3.0 User agrees to supply information the Interconnection Provider deems reasonably necessary in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice in order for it to provide the requested service. 4.0 The Interconnection Provider agrees to provide, and User agrees to take and pay for, firm transmission service over the Interconnection Facilities in accordance with the provisions of the Master Interconnection Services Agreement and this Service Agreement, with such service commencing on September 19, 2018 (the “Service Commencement Date”). 5.0 By execution of this Service Agreement, User hereby accedes to the Master Interconnection Services Agreement and shall hereafter have the rights and obligations of User thereunder with the same force and effect as if originally named as a User therein. The Master Interconnection Services Agreement is incorporated herein and made a part hereof. 6.0 Designated Representative of User: Randy Corey Chief Operating Officer (562) 348-1112 7.0 Summary of material terms of service. Big Sky North Substation Reserved Capacity: 105 MW Big Sky North Busbar Extension Reserved Capacity: 0 MW Total Reserved Capacity: 105 MW Does the User intend to install and/or use Managed Assets, e.g. a shared transformer? If so, please describe: Yes. User will install, use, and share a 34.5 / 220 kV step up transformer, current transformers, potential transformers, a 34.5 kV busbar, 34.5 kV breakers, a station service transformer, and primary and redundant fiber. Service Commencement Date: September 19, 2018 Service Term: 35 years 8.0 User (a) represents and warrants that each of the representations and warranties set forth in Section 9.1 of the Master Interconnection Services Agreement are true and correct with respect to User as of the date hereof and (b) agrees that it will perform, in accordance with the terms of the Master Interconnection Services Agreement, all the obligations that by the terms of the Master Interconnection Services Agreement are required to be performed by it as a User. [Signature page follows] IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the User and Interconnection Provider have caused this Service Agreement to be executed by their respective authorized officials effective as of the date first set forth above.
